  <h1>Privacy Policy for Pi Arcade Slots</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 16, 2025</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Pi Arcade Slots (“we,” “our,” or “us”) collects, uses, and protects user information within the Pi Network ecosystem.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do <strong>not collect personal information</strong> such as names or contact info.</li>
    <li>We store basic in-game stats and token balances using the browser's <strong>local storage</strong>.</li>
    <li>No data is transmitted or shared with third parties.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
  <p>Data is used solely to display your progress (leaderboard rank, token count, cosmetics owned). Future updates may include optional cloud saving, with your permission.</p>

  <h2>3. Data Security</h2>
  <p>All gameplay data is stored securely on your device. If Pi Wallet connection is implemented, we will comply with all Pi Network security protocols.</p>

  <h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You may clear your browser data at any time to delete local game data. We do not track users or collect external personal data.</p>

  <h2>5. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy as new features are introduced. Any updates will be posted here.</p>

  <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions, contact the developer through the Pi App Studio or in-app messaging.</p>

